result.formatted_address: 2/F, No.23 Hollywood Rd, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: The ThirtySix

reviews.text:
A fantastic Whiskey/cocktail Lounge Bar. Attentive service and my large group was there from 10 til closing (2 am). I was impressed by the consistency and never found it annoying or too much.
But what left me in awe was the "Whiskey Room", I had fun going back again again to select from a wide variety of choices on display in warm color lighting. If you like Whisky or just a relaxing atmosphere with excellent cocktails (I was helping my girlfriend finish hers lol) then this is the place for you!

2nd floor bar in the heart of Central, just opposite the newly renovated Hollywood Rd. Police HQ / art & cultural gallery. A great spot to get away from the noise on ground level. First class cocktails, extensive whisky list and comfortable interior; friendly staff as well!
Very accommodating. Great cocktails! Service is good and very different from other bars in central. Must a go to place.

on my last trip to Hong Kong, I found this gem in the middle of central. this is the place I could relax and enjoyed my favorite dark spirit: Lagavulin 16 YO, after a long day of meeting. check out their whisky vault with some hard to find whiskies for collectors.  Great place!

designed for whisky lover. 
The overall design will give you a feel of Izakaya. small bite to go with the alcohol. I see why we are referred to the highball as 'easy starter'. wow. 

the skewer offered seafood, veggi and meat. you would be able to find what you love to eat. 

highball will give you the feel of refreshing, go for the starter drink. ordered 2 to kick start. 

ice is self made with filtered water. 

1. Mamie Gilroy 110
2. Hojicha Mizuwari 140

these 2 highball, #1 with 12 years Scotch, with the lime juice and else, taste sweet and sour. Prepared you to have a meal. 
#2 would be a combination of tea and whisky, simple but original, suitable for people who love whisky.

a kind reminder: food last order at 2200

result.name: Buddha Lounge

reviews.text: A classic in the Hong Kong late night party circuit, mostly because it's open very late and a badge of honor (both for the energy and the idea of being in the "in" crowd) for staying until late morning. I'm personally of the view that it's overhyped, but if you're into tiny dance floors/bars, and techno, trance, and electro, then this might be for you.
Racist AF!
普通……
喝酒的地方。

result.formatted_address: 1/f, Amber Lodge, 23 Hollywood Rd, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Jashan Celebrating Indian Cuisine

reviews.text:
Good and fancy Indian restaurant. 
Nice mood and delicious Indian food. 
Good to go with good friends!
Came for the Sunday lunch buffet. Nothing fancy but wholesome, good quality Indian food.  Service was very good.
I love this place. Food is good to satisfy the cravings. Comfortable environment and setting. Excellent service. Will want to go back to try their lunch buffets.

Good, high quality Indian cuisine with a great set of variations when it comes to the food. Nice interiors as well with the cosier, slightly upscale touches of dark wood and dim light for the dinner service. Service overall is attentive and handles both small parties and larger groups well.
Beautiful and peaceful place for dinner. Indian restraunts outside India are like heaven for Indians.. I recommend this place to chill.

reviews.text:
Good and fancy Indian restaurant. 
Nice mood and delicious Indian food. 
Good to go with good friends!

Lunch Buffet $138，前菜、沙律、咖哩、飯、甜品、生果有齊

印度菜中裝修優雅，枱與枱之間有點距離，空間感十足，卡位可以望返大館

Dosa
DOSA 係印度薄餅，有師傅即場整，係洋蔥薯仔烤餅，入面有薯仔蓉。長長脆皮包薯仔蓉。旁邊有2款一紅一綠，紅色用蕃茄做，綠色用花生、椰子做，加上醬幾好味

前菜小食有沙律、炸蝦、

印度咖哩有六款，有羊、雞、什菜、芝士菠菜、扁豆，味道唔會好辣，每款用唔同印度香料煮，味款款唔同

最後有餐茶同生果，菠蘿西瓜都幾甜
